This paper discusses optimizations for data provenance in databases, which is a topic closely related to database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of heuristics and cost-based optimization (CBO), which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the optimizations, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR).
